docs.abstract: House votes to repeal Affordable Care Act, marking 62nd such vote but first to reach Pres Obama's desk; vote, which will force Obama to veto measure, demonstrates ability of Congressional Republicans to override united Democratic front, force that could prove crucial if next president is Republican.
